</font><font face="Times New Roman, Times" size=4 color="#000080"><b>COMMITMENT:
<br>
One 4-hour Saturday Session per month (8 total) plus 2-4 hours a month
<br>
outside of sessions with mentee pair (at mentor's discretion).<br>
<br>
</font><font face="Times New Roman, Times" size=4></div>
Each Mentor/Coach:<br>
</b>@ Supports a pair of students learning about stocks, global
economics, and personal finance.<br>
@ Coaches his/her pair towards success in a YEAH Stock Market Portfolio
Competition.<br>
@ Practices teaching and communication skills by leading lessons during
Saturday Sessions.<br>
@ Promotes students' academic and personal development in a safe,
nurturing environment.<br>
<br>
<b>Benefits for Mentors:<br>
</b>-Enhance the financial education and academic preparedness of
under-served students;<br>
-Get a crash course in stock market basics, investment strategies,
macroecon issues, etc.; <br>
-Earn a unit of academic credit for volunteering with Haas' youth
outreach program.<br>
<br>
